<br>
Anyway, I'm not meaning to &quot;troll&quot; but to debate, if you don't mind?<br>
<br>
1) Druids shouldn't get CH, I understand druids frustration about healing at HIGH end  but you are a Jack-of-all-Trades, and CH is grossly powerful, I don't think most of the druids who call for it realize what it would do or the AGGRO you would get, you'd get smashed. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> A superior HoT would surely be in character and balanced? </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->I'm unsure of Nature's Recovery's exact stats and use, but I've found it very, very good, is it good enough, or you need something better? Druids have kept me and other casters alive on AOE mobs, and I for one am very greatful of that. In XP groups druids ARE good healers when you talk about high lvl folk, yes the melee have uber hitpoints, but they ALSO have uber damage output and mitigation. Seen a druid keeping 2 monks 1 warrior all 60 high end gear going hile they chopped every mob in upper seb to bits, from D1 to chef! Group had me and a shaman as well.<br>
  I was in a group in Seb, we had shaman , planned on doing D1, got a druid, who finding he was to be main healer cried he wasn't a cleric and left, em, that's silly. Group we had was more than capable of doing that spot because I have done it before, long as the druid is competant player, with decently equipped/levelled folk and clarity (which was available), most of upper Seb is cake.<br>
<br>
2) Druid epic, yes I can see the effect, due to snare immune mobs, is a pest <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   You're epic is easy to get though, so you shouldn't have an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> UBER</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> DoT, byt this I mean like 2-3khp or such. What effect would you see as best used for the class? Call me weird but I see druids as dual natured, healer/killers, as befits Nature's two faces. Hm, would a DoT on target AND group regen spell or HoT effect not make sense and be useful?<br>
<br>
3) For those who are feeling frustrated, go play a mage post 50+ <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I love my class and have fun with it, but the gripes druids have seem small by comparison, I know that's probably a class-centered view.<br>
<br>
4) A Technique on raids you should learn is to find a friendly mage who has Rod of Mystic Transvergance spell. PTOG/skin/regen the mage, mage uses one charge of rod, drops it, so 2 charges on rod. By sharing mana and healing the mage and self from using rods, you can have AMPLE mana, either for selves or if raid needs serious mana flow. This is FAR more efficient than necro twitching, and necros should be left to  KILL mobs with their mana.<br>
<br>
5) Despite what some mages may say, I am not bothered by Dire Charm, skill of certain classes is to charm, no biggie. I do think though that the way it was implemented was wrong, a skill that would give a guaranteed duration boost on charms would be better, I think.  i.e. Level 1 = 2minutes, level 2=4 minutes, level 3 = 6 minutes. I am sure the classes who use charms could propose durations/styles that are more appropriate.<br>
<br>
6) Anti-Summoned spell, always bugged me why druids get them BEFORE mages do *scratches head*, I mean mages job is primarily SUMMONED things, yes? This isn't really a big issue but one that is odd. Oh, for those who wonder what use Banishment is, em, Icy Servants in SG, trains in the Hole, and those DAMNABLE rockfiends in the Grey (who are a nightmare for mages). Ah, the smell of shattered rockfiend in the morning! It smells like...train free zone! :&gt;<br>
  How do druids see the anti-summoned spells? Personally I think they should either have greatly improved mana/damage ratios, or be LURES. Maybe it's just my server but mobs in the Hole seem to have had a hike in resists a while back, blech! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
(friendly debate intended)<br>
